@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Pivoto" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  All tiles shown on the 7 by 7 tile board are in fact 'cubes'. When
starting a game, all the 'visible' tile faces (the front face and all
4 'sides', indicated by small rectangles on top, at right, at left
and under the front face) each have one of 5 different colours, the
backing face of each cube has the same colour as its front face.

  Clicking on a tile (or cube) will rotate the surrounding cubes so
the side face opposite of the clicked tile will rotate toward it. If
there are facing tiles of the same colour adjacent, they will then be
removed from the board and you will get points according to the
number of removed tiles.

  Avoid isolating tiles, I.E.: front facing tiles that have one
colour, but none of the neighbouring tiles have a face of the same
colour, as it would end the game...

  When a board has been cleared, then Pivoto will generate a new board
and the game will continue...

  Have fun!

